# CODEOWNERS — who must approve a PR before it can merge.
#
# Rules (GitHub evaluates top-to-bottom; LAST matching pattern wins):
#   - Default: everything requires curators review.
#   - Per-author lines below override the default for that author's dir,
#     so authors can self-merge changes inside their own /skills/<handle>/.
#   - The marketplace catalog itself (.claude-plugin/, .github/) is always
#     curators-only — authors cannot edit the catalog or CI directly.
#
# When a new contributor is onboarded, they add a line under
# "# Per-author overrides" in their first PR. The curator reviewing the
# first PR validates the handle matches the GitHub account opening the PR.

# ---- Default: curators gate everything ----
*                                   @startx-founders/curators

# ---- Curator-only paths (cannot be overridden by author lines below) ----
/.claude-plugin/                    @startx-founders/curators
/.github/                           @startx-founders/curators
/docs/                              @startx-founders/curators
/LICENSE                            @startx-founders/curators
/README.md                          @startx-founders/curators
/CONTRIBUTING.md                    @startx-founders/curators
/SECURITY.md                        @startx-founders/curators

# ---- Per-author overrides ----
# Add one line per contributor. Pattern:
#   /skills/<github-handle>/    @<github-handle>
#
# Example (uncomment + replace when first author onboards):
# /skills/mattpauker/                @mattpauker
